Package: hamwrapper
Type: Package
Title: Compiles Stan models and exposes gradients/hessians of a hamiltonian suitable for HMC
Version: 1.0
Date: 2019-08-02
Authors@R: as.person(c(
    "Arya Pourzanjani <pourzanj@gmail.com> [ctb]", 
    "Ben Bales <bbbales2@gmail.com> [ctb, cre]"
  ))
Description: This package compiles Stan models to a form so that other packages can query them for gradients,
  hessians, etc. This is meant to make it easy to experiment with different types of Bayesian inference algorithms
  from R by leaving the model specification to Stan.
License: GPL (>= 2)
Imports: Rcpp (>= 1.0.2), rstan (>= 2.19.2)
Suggests: 
    testthat (>= 2.1.0)
